# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
The issue is caused by package @angular/core (?)


### Is this a regression?

It is working in Angular 8.0.0 but fails in 8.2.3


### Description

Sometimes (e.g. for frameworks) it might be useful to automatically generate InjectionTokens for providers, e.g.:

```ts
/** Generates the token name */
export function getGeneratedToken(type: Type<any>) {
  return type.name + 'generated-stuff';
}

/** Injects with a generated token name */
export function InjectGenerated(type: Type<any>) {
  return Inject(getGeneratedToken(type))
}
```

When `Inject` isn't used directly within the constructor but inside `InjectGenerated`,
Angular throws this error:

`Uncaught TypeError: annotationCls is not a constructor`.

```ts
@Injectable()
class MyService {
  constructor(
    // This fails
    @InjectGenerated(SomeService) service: SomeService 
  ) {}
}
```

Calling Inject directly works:

```ts
@Injectable()
class MyService {
  constructor(
    @Inject(getGeneratedToken(SomeService)) service: SomeService 
  ) {}
}
```

See also [this](https://github.com/haschu/annotation-cls-error/blob/master/src/app/app.component.ts) example.

I don't know if this is an actual bug or related to a breaking change introduced into the angular compiler. But it would be great if there is least a workaround to fix this :blush:.

